---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import ServiceCTA from '../../components/ServiceCTA.astro';
---

<Layout title="Wrought Iron Gates New York | Urban Forge">
  <Header />
  
  <main class="container service-detail">
    <div class="breadcrumb">
      <a href="/services">Services</a> &gt; <span>Wrought Iron Gates</span>
    </div>
    
    <h1>Custom Wrought Iron Gates in New York</h1>
    
    <img src="/images/wrought_iron_gates.png" alt="Wrought Iron Gates" class="hero-image" />
    
    <div class="content-body">
      <h2>Bespoke Driveway, Garden, and Security Gates</h2>
      <p>A custom gate is the physical introduction to your property, defining its security, privacy, and architectural character. At Urban Forge, we design, hand-forge, and install monumental wrought iron gates for driveways, private gardens, and townhouses across New York. We combine traditional blacksmithing artistry with modern security requirements to build gates that are structurally permanent, visually stunning, and operationally reliable.</p>
      
      <h3>Traditional Blacksmithing Artistry & Details</h3>
      <p>Every gate frame and pickets run we create is forged by hand on our local anvils. Rather than relying on cast iron components that snap or bend, we forge solid wrought steel and carbon steel. We hand-form elegant details such as decorative scrolls, twisted pickets, collars, personalized monogram crests, and classical finials (like fleur-de-lis or lances). This level of hand-crafting gives the gate unique texture and lines that enhance the curb appeal of high-end estates and historic townhouses alike.</p>
      
      <h3>Historic Landmarks Regulations & Approvals</h3>
      <p>A significant portion of our work involves fabricating new or replacement gates for landmarked properties in historic NYC districts. We have deep experience working within the strict guidelines set by the Landmarks Preservation Commission (LPC). Our team performs historical research, drafts exact scaled drawings, and replicates the original profiles and dimensions of the 19th-century gate being replaced. We provide the documentation and sample materials required to ensure your landmarks board approval is fast and seamless.</p>
      
      <h3>Smart Access Control & Automation Integration</h3>
      <p>While we cherish historic craftsmanship, we recognize that modern security requires advanced technology. We engineer all of our wrought iron gates to integrate seamlessly with modern access control systems. We pre-fabricate routing channels inside the steel posts and gates to conceal wiring for:
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Automated Hinge Systems:</strong> Underground or post-mounted hydraulic arm gate operators that open via remote, keypad, or smartphone.</li>
        <li><strong>Intercom & Video Entry:</strong> Integrated camera boxes and keypads matching the hand-rubbed finish of the gate.</li>
        <li><strong>Magnetic & Solenoid Locks:</strong> Heavy-duty security locks that keep the gate securely shut and interface with home automation systems.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>Rust Prevention & Weatherproofing Finishes</h3>
      <p>Outdoor gates bear the full force of New York winters, humidity, and atmospheric pollutants. To prevent rust from taking hold in structural joints and scroll cavities, we perform a thorough weatherproofing finish. We hot-dip galvanize the entire gate assembly, coating the steel in protective liquid zinc. This is followed by a specialized epoxy primer and a topcoat of electrostatic polyurethane paint, creating a beautiful, low-maintenance finish that resists cracking and rust for decades.</p>
      <div class="architect-cta" style="background: #f9f9f9; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brushed-brass); padding: var(--spacing-md); margin: var(--spacing-xl) 0; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--spacing-md);">
        <div>
          <h4 style="margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; color: var(--color-matte-black);">Specifying this for a project?</h4>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: #555;">Download structural profiles, CAD details, and technical cut-sheets.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/architects" class="btn btn-secondary" style="font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-color: var(--color-brushed-brass); color: var(--color-brushed-brass);">Get CAD Specs (.ZIP)</a>
      </div>

      <ServiceCTA title="Ready to secure your entrance?" buttonText="Request a Gate Quote" />
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .service-detail {
    padding-block: var(--spacing-xl);
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }
  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--color-brushed-brass);
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    color: var(--color-matte-black);
  }
  .hero-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-brushed-brass);
  }
  .content-body h2, .content-body h3 {
    color: var(--color-matte-black);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  .content-body p, .content-body ul {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #444;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }
  .content-body ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  .content-body li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
